AN 18-year-old is lying in hospital while his fellow pupils are terrified of going back to school today.On Friday, two suspects known to pupils and teachers picked a fight with the grade 11 pupil at Foresthaven Secondary School in Phoenix, Durban. The pupil was moered and shot. One traumatised pupil said: &ldquo;We don&rsquo;t know what led to the shooting, but we are sure those guys are troublemakers.&rdquo; &ldquo;If dangerous people can enter the school so easily, our lives are in danger. Something needs to be done urgently.&rdquo;KZN police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said the suspects were still at large.&ldquo;The victim was shot once in his lower body before the suspects fled from the scene on foot. Phoenix police are investigating a case of attempted murder.&rdquo; KZN Education spokesman Kwazi Mthethwa said: &ldquo;We have spoken to the staff to arrange for police to monitor the school. We will also organise counselling for pupils.&rdquo;